cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.COM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper focuses on studying the achievable sum spectral efficiency of two-way half-duplex relaying system with imperfect channel estimation. This falls under the domain of information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with a relaying system where multiple pairs of single antenna users exchange information assisted by a multi-antenna relay. This involves networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper studies the power scaling law and power allocation schemes to improve the sum spectral efficiency. This involves control and optimization of the system. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with the transmission of information between multiple users, which can involve multimedia data. 
5. cs.COM (Computational Complexity): Although not the primary focus, the paper may involve computational complexity in deriving the closed-form expression for the sum spectral efficiency and designing power allocation schemes.
